Spread pie filling in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Place in cold oven. Heat oven to 400 degrees F; let heat 10 minutes. Remove pan from oven. While pie filling is heating, stir remaining ingredients until soft dough forms. Drop by 6 spoonfuls onto warm pie filling. Sprinkle with additional sugar if desired. Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until topping is light brown.